15 WHEREAS, Major Clint Morris further served in the Narcotics Unit, Criminal Investigations
16 Division, SWAT Team, Training Division, and Uniform Patrol Division, where he earned
17 the Officer of the Year Award in 2001 as well as the Purple Heart and Medal of Valor in
18 2000; and
19 WHEREAS, Captain Dee Morris served in the Narcotics Unit, Criminal Investigations
20 Division, Jail Division, Juvenile Division, and Crimes Against Children Division during her
21 distinguished tenure, earning the Officer of the Year Award in 2008; and
22 WHEREAS, in 1995, Captain Dee Morris co-founded the Paulding County CASA (Court
23 Appointed Special Advocate) program to support youth with difficult home lives, and she
24 later helped create the Family Alliance of Paulding to provide multiple services to youth,
25 including a visitation center for children in foster care; and
26 WHEREAS, Captain Dee Morris was further instrumental in developing the Junior Law
27 Enforcement Academy and professionalizing the Juvenile Division's processes and training;
28 and
29 WHEREAS, Major Clint Morris and Captain Dee Morris have served with honor and
30 distinction, and their vision and unyielding commitment to excellence in law enforcement
31 will be sorely missed; and
32 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that these remarkable Georgians be
33 appropriately honored during this special time.
